cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with deep learning models and their training in the presence of label noise, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the proposed approach is evaluated on image datasets. The paper also involves self-supervision, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cybersecurity, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
